    caption: [Four major phospholipids in mammalian plasma membranes. Different head groups are represented by different colors in the symbols. The lipid molecules shown in (A–C) are glycerophospholipids, which are derived from glycerol. The molecule in (D) is sphingomyelin, which is derived from (E) sphingosine and is therefore a sphingolipid. Note that only phosphatidylserine carries a net negative charge, the importance of which we discuss later; the other three are electrically neutral at physiological pH, carrying one positive and one negative charge.],
