    caption: [and Movie 10.3). By decreasing the mobility of the first few CH2 groups of the hydrocarbon chains of the phospho- lipid molecules, cholesterol makes the lipid bilayer less deformable in this region and thereby decreases the permeability of the bilayer to small water-soluble mol- ecules. Although cholesterol tightens the packing of the lipids in a bilayer, it does],
    path: "../fig/image_place_holder.png"
